## Failure-Mode Map

| Failure Mode | First Artifact To Check |
| --- | --- |
| Cold-start confusion or weak handoff | `progress.md`, `session-handoff.md` |
| Scope sprawl or overbuilt solution | `feature_list.json`, this roadmap, change contract |
| Premature completion or missing runtime signal | `verification-matrix.md`, `sensor-registry.md`, evidence log |
| Fragile startup or knowledge visibility gap | generated init entrypoint, fresh-session test, module docs |
| Instruction bloat or entropy growth | instruction rule lifecycle, topic-doc routing, quality document |

## Rules

- Keep roadmap entries target-relative and portable.
- Record accepted work here when it changes harness behavior, generated files,
  CI behavior, release evidence, or recurring maintenance.
- Keep candidate ideas separate from commitments.
- Do not mark work passing, validated, shipped, or complete from agent
  assertion alone; record verification evidence.
- Do not promote speculative features, abstractions, workflows, dependencies, or
  broad cleanup unless the item names them.
- Move completed behavior into durable docs, tests, schemas, templates, or code.
- Update `progress.md` and `session-handoff.md` when roadmap state changes.
- Preserve existing project-owned planning systems by linking to them.
- If localized docs exist, identify the source-of-truth locale or docs root
  before editing translated copies.
- Keep sensor and validation messages actionable for agents.
- Do not turn structural audit score into proof of real-agent effectiveness.
